oai_dc:dc.dc:title: FSU Students Meeting Governor Warren
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lee, Marjorie Fogarty
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This photograph from Spring of 1949 shows FSU students Marjorie Fogarty, Betty Jane Mattison, and Patty Crowley posing with Governor Fuller Warren in front of the Governor's Mansion in Tallahassee, Florida. This impromptu meeting resulted in having tea with the Governor and a tour of the public rooms of the mansions.

Personal photographs of Florida State University student Marjorie Fogarty Lee (formerly Marjorie Nelle Fogarty), (AB, Library Science, 1952). These photographs are a part of the Marjorie Fogarty Lee Collection, 1948-1952 (Accession No. HP-2007-014). She is the sister of class of 1950 graduate, Beverly Jean Fogarty Smith (Accession No. HP-2008-001). B/W.
